oai_dc:dc.dc:title: Marion Eddy article
oai_dc:dc.dc:subject: Eddy, Marion; aviation; newspapers;
oai_dc:dc.dc:description: An autographed copy of a 1941 New York Times article about the arrival of three Cuban goodwill fighters. Includes a photograph of Commander Watson C. Burton, Marion Eddy, Lt. Ramon Rivery, Lt. Juan Rios Montenegro, Sgt. Frank Medina, and Cayetano de Quesada y Socarras. Inscription reads, "To 'Phoebe' -- Sincerely -- Marion Eddy."
oai_dc:dc.dc:contributor: Manuscript Collection processed by Laura Cunningham
